<p>US Vice President JD Vance arrived in Israel on Tuesday to reinforce a fragile, US-brokered ceasefire in Gaza after a weekend flare-up, even as both Hamas and Israel publicly say they remain committed to the truce [nytimes.com#1][semafor.com#1][newarab.com#2]. He joins President Trump’s envoys Steve Witkoff and Jared Kushner for meetings with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on advancing the next, more complex phase of a 20-point truce plan [ft.com#1][japantoday.com#1][straitstimes.com#2][timesofisrael.com#1]. President Trump warned Hamas of “FAST, FURIOUS &amp; BRUTAL” consequences if it doesn’t comply and said allies offered to intervene in Gaza but were told to wait for now [theglobeandmail.com#1][ndtv.com#1][aljazeera.com#1]. Humanitarian needs remain acute: Gaza’s Government Media Office says fewer than 1,000 aid trucks have entered since the truce began and the UN notes deliveries are still far short of requirements [theguardian.com#1][dw.com#1]. Separately, fighters returned the body of another dead hostage under the deal, with Israeli authorities to conduct identification [newarab.com#2].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/n7vLLNn6t-10UPh5Uh5Bq25Z7MfBerMtjdyFMM4tuaRNNcc0YKCGS6JevTpNDQ6_-lVTwPxFoNgPX0MhMoVyprQmV6hEgddMh-CBGaw_lsUufUE33tDw_R2A7Vv8MNSB50c2ohnXxoUW_daMUapH36AKTTmk0z1Co7PiG4QA9ErMu59-udkszUkjPh5PleCWRE4UP-jSL3gwqxux43CiAdt5' alt='US Vice President JD Vance visits Israel as talks focus on shoring up a fragile Gaza ceasefire.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Hostage remains: Before the latest handover, Hamas had returned 12 of 28 pledged hostages’ bodies and says it needs time and technical help to recover the rest [newarab.com#2].</li><li>Israeli response: After two Israeli soldiers were killed in Gaza’s south over the weekend, Israel struck dozens of targets on Sunday using 153 tonnes of munitions and accused Hamas of a ceasefire breach [newarab.com#2].</li><li>Disarmament hurdle: A later truce phase expects Hamas to lay down arms so an international force can assume security; the group is reluctant and has reasserted authority, including executing rival militants [semafor.com#1].</li><li>Aid contents: Recent convoys reportedly carried cooking gas and diesel to power bakeries, generators, hospitals and vital services amid severe shortages, according to Gaza’s media office [theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Cairo mediation: A Hamas delegation met Egyptian and Qatari officials in Cairo to restore calm, implement the ceasefire, and prepare intra-Palestinian talks [dawn.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>We made a deal with Hamas that they&#x27;re going to be very good, they&#x27;re going to behave, they&#x27;re going to be nice - President Donald Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>United States: Washington signals it will enforce the truce and prevent escalation, with Vance’s visit adding diplomatic pressure to keep the deal on track. (<a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/10/21/vance-israel-gaza-hamas-ceasefire/'>Washington Post</a>)</li><li>Israel: The government accused Hamas of a &#x27;blatant violation&#x27; following deadly incidents and carried out strikes in response. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/vance-due-israel-us-seeks-shore-gaza-ceasefire'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Hamas: The group says it remains determined to implement the ceasefire and needs time and technical assistance to locate and return pledged remains. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/vance-due-israel-us-seeks-shore-gaza-ceasefire'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>United Nations: The UN stresses that aid entering Gaza remains far below what is needed to meet civilian needs. (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/middle-east-vance-in-israel-as-gaza-truce-hangs-in-balance/live-74437186'>DW</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/middle-east/article/3329838/us-vp-vance-arrives-israel-gaza-ceasefire-teeters-after-deadly-violence'>Can J.D. Vance’s visit to Israel cement Gaza’s 